## Necessary cookies section

cookie-settings-category-necessary-heading = Necessary
cookie-settings-category-necessary-what-are-subheading = What are necessary cookies?
cookie-settings-category-necessary-what-are-desc = Cookies that are required to support essential website features, such as logging into a secure area of a website or adding items to an online shopping basket, are considered to be necessary. These are typically not used for analytics.
cookie-settings-category-necessary-how-does-desc = { -brand-name-mozilla } uses necessary cookies only to provide essential website features, such as logging in using your { -brand-name-mozilla } account or purchasing a software subscription at checkout. Without necessary cookies, essential website features may not be able to function, so necessary cookies do not require consent.

## Functional cookies section

cookie-settings-category-functional-heading = Functional
cookie-settings-category-functional-what-are-subheading = What are functional cookies?
cookie-settings-category-functional-what-are-desc = Functional cookies remember choices you have made in the past, such as preferences you have set during a previous visit to a website. Examples might include which language you prefer reading in, or which color theme is your favorite.
cookie-settings-category-functional-how-does-desc = { -brand-name-mozilla } uses functional cookies only to try and improve your experience when visiting our websites. They are not used for analytics purposes. Functional cookies support features in a similar way to essential cookies, however a website can still operate without them. As such, you can choose whether or not you want us to collect functional cookies.

## Analytics cookies section

cookie-settings-category-analytics-heading = Analytics
cookie-settings-category-analytics-what-are-subheading = What are analytics cookies?
cookie-settings-category-analytics-what-are-desc = Analytics cookies collect information about how people use websites, such as pages visited, links clicked on, and which other website visits originated from.
cookie-settings-category-analytics-how-does-desc = { -brand-name-mozilla } uses analytics information to understand how users interact with our websites so that we can improve them, and make fixes if problems arise. We may also use data from cookies, device information, and IP addresses to help us understand how users engage with our products, services, communications, websites, online campaigns, devices, and other platforms. We will only collect analytics information and set analytics cookies if you agree to it.

## Marketing cookies section

cookie-settings-category-marketing-heading = Marketing
cookie-settings-category-marketing-what-are-subheading = What are marketing cookies?
cookie-settings-category-marketing-what-are-desc = Marketing cookies use your online activity data to help advertisers display more relevant advertising or to limit how many times you see an ad.
cookie-settings-category-marketing-how-does-desc = Marketing cookies may share information with other organizations or advertisers, so { -brand-name-mozilla } will only use them if you give consent.

